Class RobotMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • frc.robot.RobotMap
  • public final class RobotMap
extends java.lang.Object
    The purpose of the RobotMap is to state what the parts of the robot are. That's it: we are just declaring and constructing every part of the robot. There is supposed to be no logic in this file, which means the file isn't supposed to do any math or decisionmaking. This lets us to refer to the parts of the robot by what we called them in RobotMap. So, we can call the hatch solenoid hatchSolenoid instead of new DoubleSolenoid(0, 3), making the code more readable.
